comments: Caboclo (MEM) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Bradley (MEM) moves laterally into the path of James (LAL) on the drive and the contact affects his SQBR.  The contact occurs before his upward shooting motion.
Ingram (LAL) makes contact to Conley's (MEM) arm, affecting his ability to maintain control of the ball.
Noah (MEM) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Kuzma (LAL) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) engages and quickly disengages on the legal pick by Noah (MEM).
Bullock (LAL) makes contact to the body of Holiday (MEM) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Noah (MEM) does not impede Kuzma (LAL) during the rebound.
Noah (MEM) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Caldwell-Pope (LAL) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] James (LAL) hops on the same foot after he has gathered the ball.
Caboclo (MEM) makes contact to James' (LAL) arm and body, affecting his driving shot attempt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Holiday (MEM) enters the lane before the release of the free throw.
The Grizzlies obtain possession of the ball on the rebound off of the missed free throw and take more than eight seconds to establish the ball in the frontcourt.
[Observable in enhanced video] Holiday (MEM) slides his pivot foot.
Bullock (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position on Holiday (MEM) and makes clean contact with the ball on his steal attempt.
James (LAL) delivers some marginal contact to the chest of Caboclo (MEM) but the contact does not affect his ability to defend.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) makes contact to Conley's (MEM) off-arm after he has gathered the ball, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Caboclo (MEM) makes incidental contact to the body of Kuzma (LAL) after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (LAL) moves laterally into the path of Noah (MEM) and the contact affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] James (LAL) steps into the lane before the release of the free throw.
Kuzma (LAL) engages and separates with Caboclo (MEM) during the rebound.
RAR shows Noah (MEM) is in the path of James (LAL) when James initiates the contact and goes through Noah to dislodge him from his legal guarding position.
Ingram (LAL) commits a take foul on Conley (MEM).
Kuzma (LAL) establishes himself in the path of Caboclo (MEM) and briefly puts an arm around his body but immediately disengages and the contact does not affect his ability to defend the play.
LLS shows Caboclo (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by James (LAL).

The crew communicated with the Replay Center official to determine who the ball went out of bounds off of. Initially, the ruling was Grizzlies ball, and after review, the ruling was confirmed (this was called but is entered as a correct non-call so that it can be included in the last two minute report).

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Valanciunas (MEM) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.
Kuzma (LAL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Caboclo (MEM) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Ingram (LAL) and Conley (MEM) engage and disengage off-ball.
James (LAL) makes contact with the ball after the made basket, delaying the Grizzlies' chance to inbound.
Kuzma (LAL) commits a take foul on Bradley (MEM).
Noah (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by James (LAL).
